Diwali, the Festival of Lights, celebrates the victory of light over darkness and good over evil. It marks Lord Rama's return to Ayodhya after defeating Ravana, symbolizing triumph of righteousness. Key traditions include Lakshmi Puja (worship of Goddess Lakshmi for prosperity), lighting diyas, fireworks, and sharing sweets. The festival embodies inner light, positivity, and community togetherness, while recent times highlight eco-conscious celebrations.